Disney and Marvel's "Avengers: Endgame" continued to top Chinese mainland daily box office on Tuesday, according to China Movie Data Information Network. The superhero movie grossed over 250.86 million yuan (about 37.27 million US dollars). Lebanese film "Capernaum" took the second place, taking in nearly 14.85 million yuan. Coming in third was the Chinese mainland crime drama "Savage", which earned around 5.06 million yuan on its first day of release. Chinese scientists design gene-editing tool using light to kill cancer cellsAbsence at PLA maritime parade will prevent US from learning about Chinese Navy: expertsChinese American organization condemns increasing racial profiling in US Delegation of HUST attends alumni gala in Los AngelesChinese driving Vegas growthHaving fun